cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on learning general purpose distributed sentence representations. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of multi-task learning and neural networks, which are common in sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions transfer learning, which is relevant to sub-categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
